<p>KevPool Inc. ("KevPool" or "we" or "KevPool.com") is dedicated to protecting your personal information and informing you about how we use it. This privacy policy applies to transactions and activities and data gathered on any KevPool service (the "Site") including but not limited to (1) the services available under the domain and sub-domains of www.KevPool.com and (2) any KevPool "widget" or service embedded on a third-party website such as a university, company, or other organization. Please review this privacy policy periodically as we may revise it without notice. This privacy policy was last revised on October 13th, 2013. Each time you use the Site or provide us with information, by doing so you are accepting the practices described in this privacy policy at that time.<br><br>
<strong>Your IP Address</strong>
<p>Like most e-commerce Websites, each time you visit the Site, we automatically collect your IP address and the web page from which you came. In order to administer and optimize the Site for you and to diagnose problems with our Site, we use your IP address to help identify you and to gather broad demographic information about you.<br><br>
<strong>Cookies</strong>
<p>KevPool.com collects anonymous information through cookies. A cookie is a small piece of data containing a unique identification number that is sent to your browser from a Web server, and is stored on your computer's hard drive. The unique ID number identifies your browser to KevPool.com's computers whenever you visit. Cookies do not enable anyone to access personally identifiable information that you have not already given us. KevPool.com primarily uses cookies to connect members with account information stored on KevPool.com's computers. This helps KevPool.com deliver better and more personalized service. KevPool.com also uses cookies to estimate KevPool.com's audience size for advertisers; to assist in processing items in your shopping basket; to track the number of entries in KevPool.com promotions, sweepstakes and contests; to identify the areas of the site you visit; to hold session information; and to track user preferences.
Cookies are part of the technology implemented by your browser. Most browsers are initially set up to accept cookies. You can reset your browser to either notify you when you have received a cookie, or to refuse them all together.
<p>KevPool.com relies on cookies to preserve the KevPool.com identity you have created while logged on. If you set your browser to disable cookies, you may not be able to access certain areas on the Site.<br><br>
